<p>Philadelphia homeowners typically achieve solar payback periods of 12-14 years, with 25-year net savings ranging from \$15,000 to \$25,000 depending on system size and energy usage. Based on PECO's current rate of 13.9¬¢/kWh and average annual rate increases of 2.5%, a 6kW system generating 7,200 kWh annually provides immediate savings of \$1,001 in year one, growing to \$1,850 by year 25. After accounting for the federal tax credit, system degradation of 0.5% annually, and maintenance costs of approximately \$150 per year, the total 25-year return on investment averages 180-220%. Philadelphia's net metering policy ensures full retail credit for excess production during peak summer months, while SREC payments provide additional income of \$2,000-4,000 over the system lifetime. Property value increases of approximately 4% of system cost further enhance returns, adding \$7,200-9,600 to home values for typical installations.</p>

